response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Counting Duplicates\", \"description\": \"A sequence of numbers from 1 to n (inclusive) contains duplicates if at least one number appears more than once. Write a function `has_duplicates` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns `True` if the sequence from 1 to `n` contains duplicates, and `False` otherwise.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef has_duplicates(n: int) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer representing the upper bound of the sequence.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if the sequence from 1 to `n` contains duplicates, `False` otherwise.\\n\", \"code\": \"def has_duplicates(n: int) -> bool:\\n    for i in range(2, n+1):\\n        if n % i == 0 and n // i <= n:\\n            return True\\n    return False\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert has_duplicates(10) == True\", \"assert has_duplicates(11) == False\", \"assert has_duplicates(12) == True\", \"assert has_duplicates(13) == False\"] }"
